parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Line Failure due to Rust and Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Failure (Belt Separation, Blowout, or Tread Peel-Off)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire failure can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially when driving at high speeds.
The failure of the rear leaf spring shackle can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: broken or rusted rear leaf spring shackle
difficulty steering or maintaining control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to jerk forward or lose control, leading to accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: vehicle jerks forward when approaching a stop
